  "text": "Krill protein hydrolysate was prepared according to the previously described method by using pepsin according to the previously described method [CITATION_1] . Briefly, krill dry powder and pepsin at an enzyme/substrate ratio of 1:100 (w/w) were mixed, adjusted to pH 2, and then hydrolysis was carried out under continuous agitation at 37 • C for eight hours. The mixture was then heated in a 100 • C water bath for 10 min to heat-inactivate pepsin. Un-hydrolyzed proteins were removed by filtering through a filter cloth, and the filtrate was fractionated using ultrafiltration membranes to obtain three fractions: <1 kDa, 1-3 kDa, and >3 kDa using a Quixstand bench-top system (GE Healthcare, Buckinghamshire, UK). The 1-3 kDa peptide fraction (KPF) was lyophilized and used for further studies.",
